    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>But Who's Against the War Now?</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Jonathan Kutner letter disputes David Rieff's March 25 article on Democratic presidential candidates' views on Iran's nuclear threat</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>David Rieff paints what he calls ''Democratic antiwar protesters'' with too broad a brush (March 25). Many of us protest the Iraq war for its futility rather than as a retreat from American influence and power in the region. A drawdown would enable us to confront the larger Iranian threat without being exposed and weakened by our involvement in Iraq.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>David Rieff paints what he calls ''Democratic antiwar protesters'' with too broad a brush (March 25). Many of us protest the Iraq war for its futility rather than as a retreat from American influence and power in the region. A drawdown would enable us to confront the larger Iranian threat without being exposed and weakened by our involvement in Iraq.</p>
